{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01QExKvcA6NqL3ga9p8pxeAw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete and verified.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Problem:** After a permissions change, `reporting-user` had been granted the `rawRead` role (find on `appdb.raw`) — the wrong collection. It had **no** access to `appdb.reports`, so dashboards failed, while it *could* read `appdb.raw`, which must stay hidden.\n\n**Fix applied** (via `admin-user` on the replica set, no operators/CRDs):\n1. Created a minimal custom role `reportsRead` on `appdb` granting only `find` on `appdb.reports`.\n2. Granted `reportsRead` to `reporting-user`.\n3. Revoked the `rawRead` role from `reporting-user`.\n\n**Verified** as `reporting-user`:\n- `appdb.reports` → readable (3 docs) ✅\n- `appdb.raw` → `Unauthorized` (denied) ✅\n\n`reporting-user` now has exactly the minimum access needed for the dashboards and nothing more."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":732,"cache_read_input_tokens":35733,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":732},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3c3c78d6-1a3d-4e69-9053-c25d4e5c32c2","uuid":"d4310740-c3f3-42c8-85da-4918838820e4","request_id":"req_011CcAu2Jp9Bju6siuP6ZL51"}
